text.tspan: Specify a bounding box (decimal degree) and the elevation
describing your data. The sliders can either be dragged
or filled in with a value.
Specify the name of the location or close by locations the
data comes from. The green fields are linked to services
(GeoNames) which help you fill out the forms providing you
with suggestions. Add with the plus button.
The spatial raster specifies the coverage and the resolution
of the data. An example would be a setup that spreads across
a whole continent with plot size study areas.
(point: m^2, plot: 1 m^2 - 0.01 km^2, region: 0.01 km^2 - 10.000 km^2,
